# my_prompt Access Policy

- Treat `my_prompt/` as private local data.
- Hard deny by default: never run tools against `my_prompt/` (read/search/edit/delete/shell path targeting).
- If access appears necessary, stop and ask for explicit one-time approval in the current turn.
- Never include `my_prompt/` contents in patches, commits, terminal output summaries, or generated docs.
- Keep `my_prompt/` excluded from AI context indexing via repository `.cursorignore`.
